# Environment and Configuration

## env.sh is optional

`env.sh` no longer sets compiler variables — bundled SQLite compiles with any
standard C compiler on PATH. Source it only if you want the convenience path
exports.

## Environment Variables

```bash
# All optional — the app runs with nothing set.
export LEMONADE_URL="http://localhost:13305/api/v1"  # Only needed for non-default server URL
export UFORGE_SCHEMA_DIR="./defaults/schemas"        # Override schema directory
export UFORGE_DATA_FILE="./defaults/data/memory.jsonl" # Override data file
export RUST_LOG=info                                 # Log verbosity

# Integration test control (default: auto-skip when no server found)
export UFORGE_INTEGRATION_TESTS=require  # Panic instead of skip when server unreachable
export UFORGE_INTEGRATION_TESTS=skip     # Force-skip even when a server is present
```

### Why env vars are overrides, not requirements

`cargo run -p u-forge-ui-gpui` must work with zero env vars set. An unset env
var must never be a hard error for core functionality.
`lemonade::resolve_lemonade_url()` encodes this — never `env::var(...).unwrap()`
at the top level.

### Module-specific logging

```bash
export RUST_LOG=u_forge_core::graph::storage=debug,u_forge_core::ai::embeddings=info
```

## Path Resolution

### Schema Directory (checked in order)
1. `$UFORGE_SCHEMA_DIR`
2. `./defaults/schemas`
3. `../defaults/schemas`

### Data File (checked in order)
1. `$UFORGE_DATA_FILE`
2. `./defaults/data/memory.jsonl`
3. `../defaults/data/memory.jsonl`

## Database Location

`KnowledgeGraph::new(db_path)` opens (or creates) a SQLite database at
`<db_path>/knowledge.db`. The directory is created automatically.

The desktop app uses a persistent database. Set `UFORGE_DATA_FILE` /
`UFORGE_SCHEMA_DIR` to customise import sources.

