## Lemonade Server

Lemonade Server provides all AI inference (embedding, reranking, chat, STT,
TTS) via an OpenAI-compatible HTTP API. u-forge.ai does **not** fall back to a
local model if Lemonade is unavailable — features degrade gracefully and a
clear error is returned to the user.

### Setup

```bash
# Install (Linux via snap)
sudo snap install lemonade-server

# Pull required models
lemonade-server pull embed-gemma-300m-FLM      # embeddings (NPU, 0.62 GB) — default
lemonade-server pull whisper-v3-turbo-FLM      # transcription (NPU, 1.55 GB)
lemonade-server pull bge-reranker-v2-m3-GGUF   # reranking (GPU/CPU)

# Start
lemonade-server serve

# Verify — also shows which models are currently loaded in RAM
curl http://localhost:13305/api/v1/health
```

Cross-platform Lemonade install: Linux → `snap`; macOS → `.pkg` from GitHub
releases; Windows → `.exe` installer.

### URL Resolution Order

`lemonade::resolve_lemonade_url()`:
1. `GET http://localhost:13305/api/v1/health` — probed with 2 s timeout
2. `GET http://127.0.0.1:13305/api/v1/health` — explicit IPv4 loopback
3. `LEMONADE_URL` env var — accepted as-is, no liveness check

Returns `None` when no server is found. Setting `LEMONADE_URL` is optional when
Lemonade runs on its default port.

### Endpoints in Use

| Endpoint | Method | Provider / Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `/api/v1/models` | GET | `LemonadeServerCatalog::discover()` |
| `/system-info` | GET | `LemonadeServerCatalog::discover()` — installed backends |
| `/api/v1/health` | GET | `LemonadeServerCatalog::discover()` + manual verification |
| `/api/v1/load` | POST | `load_model()` — load a model before inference |
| `/api/v1/embeddings` | POST (JSON) | `LemonadeProvider` |
| `/api/v1/audio/transcriptions` | POST (multipart) | `LemonadeTranscriptionProvider` (no GPU lock) / `LemonadeSttProvider` (GPU-managed) |
| `/api/v1/audio/speech` | POST (JSON) | `LemonadeTtsProvider` |
| `/api/v1/chat/completions` | POST (JSON) | `LemonadeChatProvider` |
| `/api/v1/reranking` | POST (JSON) | `LemonadeRerankProvider` |

### Why two transcription providers

`LemonadeTranscriptionProvider` has no GPU resource management — suitable for
NPU FLM whisper and standalone use. `LemonadeSttProvider` integrates with
`GpuResourceManager` to prevent contention when LLM inference runs concurrently
on the same GPU. Both are constructed via `ProviderFactory::build` with
`Capability::Transcription`. Choice is based on whether GPU contention is
possible, not ergonomic preference.

